==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Curled
<hw>Curled</hw> <pr>(k⟦ucir⟧rld)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having curls;
curly; sinuous; wavy; <as>as, <ex>curled</ex> maple (maple having fibers
which take a sinuous course)</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Curled hair</b></col> <fld>(Com.)</fld>, <cd>the hair of
the manes and tails of horses, prepared for upholstery purposes.</cd>
<rj><au>McElrath.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Curledness</ent>⟦br⟧
